# Files EAS Build should NOT upload to the cloud builder.
#
# EAS uses this file INSTEAD of .gitignore when it exists. That lets us keep
# google-services.json and .env out of GitHub (still listed in .gitignore) while
# STILL shipping them to our own private EAS build, which needs them:
#   - google-services.json  -> required by android.googleServicesFile at prebuild
#   - .env                  -> EXPO_PUBLIC_* values inlined into the app bundle
# (Both are referenced here only by their ABSENCE — anything not listed uploads.)

# Dependencies & build output (don't upload — EAS reinstalls/rebuilds)
node_modules/
.expo/
dist/
web-build/
.git/

# Dev cruft
.metro-health-check*
*.tsbuildinfo
.DS_Store
npm-debug.*
yarn-debug.*
yarn-error.*
app-example

# NEVER upload signing / service-account secrets
*.jks
*.p8
*.p12
*.key
*.mobileprovision
*-firebase-adminsdk-*.json
